                type="document" xml:id="d1">
                <head>No. 1<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 30, Senators Fulbright, <persName corresp="#p_MCMAHONB1"
                        >McMahon</persName>, and <persName>Sparkman</persName> sent a letter to
                    President <persName corresp="#p_TRUMANHS1">Truman</persName> concerning a
                    resolution which they intended to introduce in the Senate. The resolution called
                    upon the President to take positive steps to encourage the political federation
                    of Europe. For the text of this letter and President <persName
                        corresp="#p_TRUMANHS1">Truman</persName>’s response to it, as well as the
                    text of the resolution which was introduced in the Senate on January 31 as
                    Senate Resolution 269, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                    February 18, 1952, pages 275–276.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
